{{Infobox Ghana constituency | Name = Asene Akroso-Manso | Map1 = <!-- Map of constituency location in district--> | Map2 = Ghana-Eastern | Year = | District = [[Birim Central Municipal District]] | Region = [[Eastern Region, Ghana|Eastern Region]] | MP = [[George Kwame Aboagye]] | Party = [[New Patriotic Party]] }}
'''Asene Akroso-Manso''' is one of the [[Constituency|constituencies]] represented in the [[Parliament of Ghana]]. It elects one [[Member of Parliament|Member of Parliament (MP)]] by the [[first past the post]] system of election.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanaelections.peacefmonline.com/pages/2016/eastern/294/|title=Ghana Election 2016 Results - Asene Akroso Monso Constituency|last=FM|first=Peace|website=Ghana Elections - Peace FM|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref> Asene Akroso-Manso was one of the constituencies created before the 2012 general elections in Ghana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanaelections.peacefmonline.com/pages/2012/eastern/294/|title=Ghana Election 2012 Results - Asene Akroso Monso Constituency|last=FM|first=Peace|website=Ghana Elections - Peace FM|access-date=2018-04-14}}</ref>
==Boundaries== The seat is located entirely within the Birim Central Municipal Assembly of the Eastern Region of Ghana.
