'''''Combate''''' or ''O Jornal Combate'' was a [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] newspaper published in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]].<ref name=pm>{{cite web|title=Portugal: The Impossible Revolution?|url=http://secure.pmpress.org/index.php?l=product_detail&p=377|work=PM Press|accessdate=8 June 2016}}</ref> It existed between June 1974 to February 1978.<ref name="mar"/>
==History and profile== The first edition of ''Combate'' appeared on 21 June 1974.<ref name="lib">{{cite news|title=O Jornal Combate|url=https://libcom.org/history/o-jornal-combate|accessdate=8 June 2016|work=Libcom|date=8 July 2015}}</ref> The paper had a [[Marxist]] stance.<ref name="mar">{{cite web|title=Combate|url=https://www.marxists.org/portugues/tematica/jornais/combate/index.htm|publisher=Marxists|accessdate=8 June 2016|language=Portuguese}}</ref> Phil Mailer served as the editor of the paper.<ref name=pm/> The first ten issues were published weekly.<ref name=lib/> The remaining issues appeared fortnightly with interruptions until February 1978 when the paper ceased publication.<ref name=lib/>
