{{Infobox university |name = Iqra Institute for Higher Education |native_name = <span lang="ar">'''اقرأ للتعليم العالي''' |image_name = IqraBadhan3.jpg |caption = |motto = |mottoeng = ''Baro saad u noolaatid'' |established = 2008 |city = [[Badhan, Sanaag|Badhan]] |country = [[Somalia]] |endowment = $ 21,230 |campus = Urban and suburban |staff = 17 |chancellor = Prof Abdurashid Sheikh Salah |vice_chancellor = |affiliations = |free_label = |free = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |website = }}
'''''Iqra Institute for Higher Education''''' is a Somali institute for higher education situated in the town of [[Badhan, Sanaag|Badhan]], in the [[Sanaag]] ([[Maakhir]]) Region of [[Somalia]]. The institute was established in 2008 on the basis of providing opportunities for destitute youth in the region of [[Sanaag]], focusing on vocational courses and other short courses in Management and languages, for its students to reduce poverty, and develop educated individuals who, in return, will help the community with their struggle against poverty.<ref>[http://somalitalk.com/2010/02/14/warbixin-xaggee-marayaa-machadka-iqra-institute-for-higher-education-kana-qayb-qaadoo-dhameystirkiisa- Xagee marayaa Machadka Iqra (Somali)]</ref>
==Overview== The [[Sanaag]] ([[Maakhir]]) region has been subjected to a prolonged lack of any higher educational entity, possibly as a result of the long and devastating [[Somali civil war]], which have had multiple impacts on the local youth, and devastating effects on career developments and the possibility of youth receiving sustainable income.<ref>[http://www.beps.net/publications/SomaliaEducationSectorAssessmentFinalReport.doc.pdf Education in Somalia]</ref>
Youths have become destitute in high numbers. Harsh socio-economic conditions and lack of higher education have, in turn, escalated their poverty and increased the likelihood of the youths immigrating to other regions of [[Somalia]] to seek further education. The area is huge and lacks basic community institutions in surrounding towns or cities.<ref>[http://www.unicef.org/somalia/education.html UNICEF's assessment on education in Somalia]</ref>
The institute offers different types of courses and vocational skill lessons on its main campus in [[Badhan, Sanaag|Badhan]]. The institute has joined the Union of Somali institutes, a consortium of Somalia's institutes.<ref>[http://spr.fm/index.php?option=com_k2&view=item&id=2444:dhegeyso-machadka-iqra-ee-magaalada-badhan-oo-ku-biray-midawga-macaahida-soomaliyeed&Itemid=139- Iqra joins Union of Somali institutes (Somali)]</ref>
