'''Rada''' is a major family of [[loa]] in [[Haitian Vodou]]. ==Scope== They include older, beneficent spirits who can be directly traced to [[Dahomey]] [[West African Vodun|Vudus]] of West Africa.
==Etymology== "Rada" is a [[cognate]] of [[Arará]], and also [[Yoruba mythology|Yoruba]] [[orisha]]s.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.manigua.org/resources/orishas/legba_ghede.html |title= Manigua.org: Loa of Vodou |accessdate= June 9, 2006 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20060720164803/http://www.manigua.org/resources/orishas/legba_ghede.html |archivedate= July 20, 2006 |deadurl= yes |df= }}</ref>
==Function== Rada loas are guardians of [[ethics|morals and principles]], related to Africa, whereas [[Petro loa]]s are connected to the [[New World]] of the [[Western hemisphere|West]], and are considered more aggressive. Some loas (such as [[Erzulie]]) have both Rada and Petro manifestations.
==Identities== Some Rada loa are: [[Papa Legba|Legba]], [[Loco (loa)|Loco]], [[Ayizan]], [[Anaisa Pye]], [[Damballa]], [[Ayida-Weddo]], [[Erzulie]], and [[Agwé]].
