{{advert|date=May 2016}} {{notability|Companies|date=May 2016}} '''The Danish Trade Council''' is a trade organisation within the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of [[Denmark]] to promote Danish exports and investment abroad. The Council has an office in [[Copenhagen]] that houses roughly 100 employees, and also employs another 300 people at embassies, consulates, and trade commissions worldwide. The Council works to expand Danish exports and investment worldwide by offering Danish companies advise on international activities. The Council also publishes annual report on its activities. <div> '''The Danish Trade Council in UK''' <div> The Danish Trade Council in UK is located at the [[Danish Embassy]], where it creates value, growth and knowledge for Denmark through consulting services and partnerships. Being the third largest export market for Denmark, it is crucial for Danish companies to look at the British market, and this is where the Danish Trade Council can provide professional consulting. The Danish Trade Council in the UK also assist UK companies to get in contact Danish exporters. <div> ''Exporting to Denmark'' UK eksporters wishing to market their products/services in Denmark should contact UK Trade and Invest, www.uktradeinvest.gov.uk or the British Embassy in Denmark, www.britishembassy.dk.
<ref>{{cite web|title=The Danish Trade Council|url=http://um.dk/en/tradecouncil/about/org/|accessdate=2012-03-08}}</ref>
