{{Infobox organization | name = Xaveri Burundi | image = | size = 250px | caption = | abbreviation= | formation = | type = Burundi non-profit youth organization | location = {{Flag|Burundi}} | purpose = Catholic youth organization | headquarters = {{Flag|Burundi}} | membership = 26,000 | leader_title2 = Presidents | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = Praeses | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = Secretary-General | leader_name4 = | website = }}
Xaveri Burundi is a Catholic youth organization in the [[Burundi]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TENqSwAACAAJ|title=Perspectives de pastorale urbaine et spécialisée au Burundi et apport du mouvement Xaveri|last=Kameya|first=André|date=1986-01-01|publisher=Pontificia Università lateranense|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1AweyrSzqFMC|title=Landenreeks Burundi|last=Berwouts|first=K.|date=2006-12-31|publisher=KIT Publishers|isbn=9789068324303|language=nl}}</ref> Xaveri Burundi is part of the African Xaveri Movement and a member of the Catholic umbrella of youth organizations [[Fimcap]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://fimcap.org/fr/afrique/xaveri-burundi|title=Xavieri Burundi|website=fimcap.org|access-date=2016-06-09}}</ref>
== History == Xaveri Burundi was founded in 1953 by Reverend Frère Geolf.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://xaveriburundi.blogspot.de/2012/01/historique.html|title=Charité..................Toujours: Historique mouvement xavéri au Burundi|website=xaveriburundi.blogspot.de|access-date=2016-06-09}}</ref>
